file precedence in splunk.


linux comands:
1. ls: list all the files/directory in a directory.
2. cd: change directory.
3. rm: remove a file
4. cat: check contents of a file
5. mkdir: creates directory. eg. mkdir srabani
6. cp: copy. eg. cp /opt/splunk_training.txt /opt/srabani/
7. tar: cvfz(compress verbose file zip)  xvfz(extract verbose file zip)
eg. tar xvfz splunkforwarder-9.2.1-78803f08aabb-Linux-x86_64.tgz
8. ifconfig: you can see ip configuration. 
9. wget: download file from internet.
 wget -O splunk-9.2.1-78803f08aabb-Linux-x86_64.tgz "https://download.splunk.com/products/splunk/releases/9.2.1/linux/splunk-9.2.1-78803f08aabb-Linux-x86_64.tgz"
10. init: init 0: shut down. init 6: restart
11. pwd: present working directory
12. history: list of used commands
13. whoami: shows username
15. ping: is used to check internet connection.
16. df: check free disk space.
17. rmdir: remove a directory.
18. clear: clear the screen.
19. exit: exit from one user.
20. log out:
21. sudo su: superuser do

change file ownership:
chown -R root:root splunkforwarder

vi editor commands:
vi <file> -> creates file
i -> insert mode
esc ->command mode
:wq -> save and quit
:q ->quit
shift g -> bottom of the file
yy-> copy the line where the control is
3/4yy -> copy 3/4 lines
p-> paste line
dd -> cut line
/keyword -> search the keyword.
2u -> undo 2 changes.

%s/<keyword>/<new_keyword>/g
